255
00:13:30,811 --> 00:13:33,047
Hisoka: No. I’ve had enough fun.

256
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,683
Killua: Hey, why don’t you
stick around and join us?

257
00:13:35,716 --> 00:13:38,586
I wanna know
what the troupe is up to.

258
00:13:38,619 --> 00:13:42,590
Hisoka: Oh, i’m not interested
in collecting cards,

259
00:13:42,623 --> 00:13:45,626
but contact me
if anything else comes up.

260
00:13:45,659 --> 00:13:49,630
I’ll cast accompany or
magnetic force to fly over.

261
00:13:51,064 --> 00:13:52,098
( Killua gasps )

262
00:13:52,132 --> 00:13:54,334
Gon: Hmm? Huh?

263
00:13:54,368 --> 00:13:56,036
Killua: That jerk.
He lied to us!

264
00:13:56,069 --> 00:13:57,404
Gon: Huh?

265
00:13:57,437 --> 00:13:59,272
Killua: We haven’t used
magnetic force at all

266
00:13:59,306 --> 00:14:01,341
since hisoka teamed up with us.
Am I right?

267
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:02,509
Gon: Uh-huh.

268
00:14:02,543 --> 00:14:04,445
Killua: That means
when he ran into us,

269
00:14:04,478 --> 00:14:06,213
that he already knew
about spell cards.

270
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:07,414
- Get it?
- Gon: Huh?

271
00:14:08,415 --> 00:14:09,416
Bisky: Killua...

272
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:10,750
There are some liars

273
00:14:10,784 --> 00:14:13,153
who only lie when there’s
a good reason to,

274
00:14:13,187 --> 00:14:14,355
and then there are those

275
00:14:14,388 --> 00:14:16,490
who will lie
without any reason at all.

276
00:14:16,523 --> 00:14:19,626
You and I are the former,
but hisoka’s the latter.

277
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:21,695
And fretting
won’t get you anywhere.

278
00:14:21,728 --> 00:14:23,597
- Accept it.
- ( Killua groans )

279
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:24,631
( Chime rings )

280
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:26,834
Binder: Attention.

281
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:29,436
Another player
has cast contact on you.

282
00:14:29,469 --> 00:14:31,137
Genthru: It’s been a while.

283
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:32,839
Do you know who this is?

284
00:14:32,873 --> 00:14:34,341
Tsezgerra: Genthru.

285
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:36,276
What do you want?

286
00:14:36,310 --> 00:14:38,612
Genthru: First, i’d like
to congratulate you.

287
00:14:38,645 --> 00:14:40,347
Tsezgerra: What do you mean?

288
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:41,414
( Genthru chuckles )

289
00:14:41,448 --> 00:14:43,150
Ah, don’t play dumb.

290
00:14:43,183 --> 00:14:46,186
So here’s the deal.
I promise to spare your lives,

291
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:49,156
and you hand over
the strip of beach in return.

292
00:14:49,189 --> 00:14:50,590
Tsezgerra: That’s ridiculous.

293
00:14:50,624 --> 00:14:51,825
( Genthru chuckles )

294
00:14:51,859 --> 00:14:54,528
Well, I must admit
I am somewhat interested

295
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:56,530
to see if you can beat us.

296
00:14:57,698 --> 00:15:00,167
If you’re willing
to make a deal,

297
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:03,770
then come alone to masadora’s
entrance gate in one hour.

298
00:15:03,804 --> 00:15:07,775
If you don’t,
we’ll take the card by force.

299
00:15:07,808 --> 00:15:10,778
Oh, and don’t bother running
or trying to hide.

300
00:15:10,811 --> 00:15:13,180
We have a lot of accompanies.

301
00:15:13,213 --> 00:15:14,548
( Laughs )

302
00:15:14,581 --> 00:15:16,650
Tsezgerra: How?
I knew he’d find out,

303
00:15:16,683 --> 00:15:19,452
but I never thought
it would be so soon.

304
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:21,521
- Genthru: Asta, amana...
- Tsezgerra: Huh?

305
00:15:21,555 --> 00:15:24,458
Genthru: Manheim, Nick cue,

306
00:15:24,491 --> 00:15:27,294
souheil, kazsule...

307
00:15:27,327 --> 00:15:31,798
They were all members
of your party of 15, correct?

308
00:15:31,832 --> 00:15:33,867
If you’ll
just check your binder,

309
00:15:33,901 --> 00:15:36,604
you’ll notice
that they’re no longer with us.

310
00:15:36,637 --> 00:15:37,605
Tsezgerra: What?!

311
00:15:37,638 --> 00:15:38,806
Gon: Book!

312
00:15:38,839 --> 00:15:41,208
This means they’re either dead

313
00:15:41,241 --> 00:15:43,810
or they’re not
in the game anymore.

314
00:15:43,844 --> 00:15:47,214
( Gasping )

315
00:15:47,247 --> 00:15:49,216
- Genthru!
- Genthru: Hmm?

316
00:15:49,249 --> 00:15:50,517
Who are you?

317
00:15:50,551 --> 00:15:52,153
Gon: I’m gon freecss,

318
00:15:52,186 --> 00:15:53,821
and i’m ready to take you on!

319
00:15:53,854 --> 00:15:55,723
( Both gasp )

320
00:15:55,756 --> 00:15:57,524
Genthru: Gon, huh?

321
00:15:57,558 --> 00:15:59,827
So you’re one
of those three brats.

322
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:02,730
I see you have
wild luck alexandrite.

323
00:16:02,763 --> 00:16:05,499
I’ll find you
when i’m done with tsezguerra,

324
00:16:05,532 --> 00:16:08,235
unless you want
to give up the card now.

325
00:16:08,268 --> 00:16:10,670
Gon: Get over here right now!
I wanna fight you!

326
00:16:10,704 --> 00:16:11,872
I also have--

327
00:16:11,905 --> 00:16:13,340
- killua: Gon!
- ( Bisky yelling )

328
00:16:13,373 --> 00:16:15,942
Killua: Tsezguerra,
talk somewhere else!

329
00:16:15,976 --> 00:16:17,277
( Owl hoots )

330
00:16:17,311 --> 00:16:19,180
( Chime rings )

331
00:16:19,213 --> 00:16:20,347
Binder: Attention.

332
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:23,683
Another player
has cast contact on you.

333
00:16:23,717 --> 00:16:26,453
Phinks: This is phinks.
We found him.

334
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:29,189
We’re heading in your direction
as we speak.

335
00:16:29,223 --> 00:16:31,358
( Hisoka chuckles )

336
00:16:31,391 --> 00:16:34,227
Bara: Wouldn’t it be faster
to target the kids?

337
00:16:34,261 --> 00:16:36,964
They probably don’t have
the original strip of beach,

338
00:16:36,997 --> 00:16:39,766
but I bet they got a copy.

339
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:43,504
Genthru: If so, it would be
a card created by clone.

340
00:16:43,537 --> 00:16:45,372
Bara: Yeah, you’re right.

341
00:16:45,405 --> 00:16:48,241
Genthru: Once those kids
see tsezguerra surrender,

342
00:16:48,275 --> 00:16:50,778
they’ll give up
without a fight.

343
00:16:50,811 --> 00:16:52,746
If we target the brats,

344
00:16:52,779 --> 00:16:54,748
tsezguerra will have
time to recover,

345
00:16:54,781 --> 00:16:56,516
which could be
rather troublesome.

346
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:58,752
He’s a single-star hunter,
after all,

347
00:16:58,785 --> 00:17:01,788
and we don’t know
what his ability is.

348
00:17:01,822 --> 00:17:05,392
Tsezgerra: Genthru doesn’t know
what you’re capable of.

349
00:17:05,425 --> 00:17:06,927
He and his team assume

350
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,663
that we have
the original strip of beach,

351
00:17:09,696 --> 00:17:12,399
and that could prove
to be very helpful.

352
00:17:12,432 --> 00:17:15,669
So they’re after what they
think is the original card,

353
00:17:15,702 --> 00:17:17,003
the one we have.

354
00:17:17,037 --> 00:17:20,007
We’ll buy you
as much time as possible.

355
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,409
Use it to regain your strength.

356
00:17:22,442 --> 00:17:24,511
If you want to beat this game,

357
00:17:24,545 --> 00:17:26,814
you’ll have no choice
but to fight them.

358
00:17:26,847 --> 00:17:30,317
You’re the only ones
with a chance of beating them.

359
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:32,018
There’s no doubt in my mind.

360
00:17:32,052 --> 00:17:36,690
But, gon, what you did
just now was selfish.

361
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:39,426
But more than that,
it was incredibly foolish.

362
00:17:39,459 --> 00:17:41,728
If they had accepted
your challenge and come,

363
00:17:41,762 --> 00:17:43,564
what would have happened
to killua,

364
00:17:43,597 --> 00:17:45,566
given the extent
of his injuries?

365
00:17:45,599 --> 00:17:47,434
( Gon grunts )

366
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:49,736
Tsezgerra: By losing control
of your emotions,

367
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:51,972
you endangered
not only yourself,

368
00:17:52,005 --> 00:17:54,574
but your friends, too.

369
00:17:54,608 --> 00:17:56,643
I’m really sorry.

370
00:17:56,677 --> 00:17:58,913
Tsezgerra: That aside,

371
00:17:58,946 --> 00:18:01,048
it will all
come down to accompany.

372
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:03,350
If we can stave off
their pursuit,

373
00:18:03,383 --> 00:18:05,852
we should be able
to buy plenty of time.

374
00:18:05,886 --> 00:18:08,489
But if we let
too much time pass,

375
00:18:08,522 --> 00:18:10,958
then they might
just decide to change things

376
00:18:10,991 --> 00:18:12,626
and target you instead.

377
00:18:12,659 --> 00:18:14,361
We probably have a week.

378
00:18:14,394 --> 00:18:16,363
More, and you’re on your own.

379
00:18:16,396 --> 00:18:19,866
Killua: One week.
That’s not very long,

380
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,336
and, to be honest,
it’s probably optimistic.

381
00:18:22,369 --> 00:18:24,671
They might even decide
to focus on us

382
00:18:24,705 --> 00:18:27,374
after only three days or so.

383
00:18:27,407 --> 00:18:29,342
Goreinu: Then i’ll team up
with tsezguerra.

384
00:18:29,376 --> 00:18:31,578
What about you?
What are you gonna do?

385
00:18:31,612 --> 00:18:32,947
If we’re buying you time,

386
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:34,748
that implies
we have an alliance.

387
00:18:34,781 --> 00:18:36,383
Tsezgerra: Wait.

388
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:39,586
There’s very little benefit
in allying with them,

389
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:41,589
especially now
that the enemy knows

390
00:18:41,622 --> 00:18:43,991
that the eight of us
have been working together.

391
00:18:44,024 --> 00:18:46,326
And that being the case,

392
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:48,062
we won’t be able
to act as decoys

393
00:18:48,095 --> 00:18:49,797
while you take out genthru,

394
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:52,499
so of course
we’ll have to be careful

395
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:54,735
with the two cards
they still lack,

396
00:18:54,768 --> 00:18:57,070
both number two and number 75.

397
00:18:57,104 --> 00:19:00,074
Leaving them with any one party
would be dangerous,

398
00:19:00,107 --> 00:19:01,909
and we can’t afford the risk.

399
00:19:01,942 --> 00:19:05,979
That means that my offer
to buy time isn’t an alliance.

400
00:19:06,013 --> 00:19:08,449
What i’m offering you
is a trade.

401
00:19:08,482 --> 00:19:09,717
Gon: A trade, huh?

402
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:10,985
Tsezgerra: Just three weeks,

403
00:19:11,018 --> 00:19:13,721
that’s all the time
we can buy you,

404
00:19:13,754 --> 00:19:15,522
and if we succeed,

405
00:19:15,556 --> 00:19:19,627
you’ll give us number 75,
the wild luck alexandrite card.

406
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:21,028
Killua: I don’t get it.

407
00:19:21,061 --> 00:19:23,931
You just said
you could only buy us a week.

408
00:19:23,964 --> 00:19:25,098
Tsezgerra: Well, that’s assuming

409
00:19:25,132 --> 00:19:27,134
that we stay on the run
for that long.

410
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:31,705
If necessary, I may be able
to force a stalemate of sorts.

411
00:19:31,738 --> 00:19:32,973
Killua: Oh, I see.

412
00:19:33,006 --> 00:19:34,808
But if you guys
really want 75,

413
00:19:34,842 --> 00:19:37,845
we’ll just tell you how
you can get your hands on it.

414
00:19:37,878 --> 00:19:40,948
Tsezgerra: No. We’re well aware
of how to obtain it.

415
00:19:40,981 --> 00:19:44,151
Some of us only have
a few empty slots left,

416
00:19:44,184 --> 00:19:45,852
and that’s including goreinu.

417
00:19:45,886 --> 00:19:48,989
We would be required
to turn all of our cards over

418
00:19:49,022 --> 00:19:52,425
to the villagers,
and that’s no longer reasonable.

419
00:19:52,459 --> 00:19:54,461
Three weeks.

420
00:19:54,494 --> 00:19:57,931
But that isn’t nearly enough
time for killua’s hands to heal

421
00:19:57,965 --> 00:20:02,570
or to close the gap between our
abilities and those of genthru.

422
00:20:02,603 --> 00:20:04,805
Killua: So we
should use that time

423
00:20:04,838 --> 00:20:06,973
to come up with
a workable strategy.

424
00:20:07,007 --> 00:20:08,775
Tsezgerra: Yes, exactly.

425
00:20:08,809 --> 00:20:11,412
Devise a scenario
that you can win.

426
00:20:11,445 --> 00:20:13,781
Identify the circumstances,

427
00:20:13,814 --> 00:20:16,684
and then prepare
to carry out the strategy.

428
00:20:16,717 --> 00:20:18,719
♪

429
00:20:20,888 --> 00:20:22,089
Gon: We got it.

430
00:20:22,122 --> 00:20:24,024
Tsezgerra: Good.
We’ll leave now

431
00:20:24,057 --> 00:20:26,493
and delay team genthru
all we can.

432
00:20:26,527 --> 00:20:27,561
( Goreinu grunts )

433
00:20:27,594 --> 00:20:29,096
Tsezgerra:
And never forget, gon,

434
00:20:29,129 --> 00:20:33,700
they’ve killed over 50 players
in this game so far.

435
00:20:33,734 --> 00:20:36,036
If you truly want
to beat the game,

436
00:20:36,069 --> 00:20:37,904
you’ll have to fight them.

437
00:20:39,039 --> 00:20:40,507
( Gon grunts )

438
00:20:40,541 --> 00:20:43,611
Tsezgerra: Accompany on!
To masadora!

439
00:20:46,647 --> 00:20:48,149
Bisky: Just three weeks?

440
00:20:48,182 --> 00:20:50,584
That sure isn’t very much time.

441
00:20:50,617 --> 00:20:53,753
Killua, you focus on healing.
While you’re doing that,

442
00:20:53,787 --> 00:20:56,023
think of a strategy
to help us beat genthru.

443
00:20:56,056 --> 00:20:57,190
Killua: Right.

444
00:20:57,224 --> 00:20:58,992
Bisky: Gon,
you’ll train with me.

445
00:20:59,026 --> 00:21:02,763
If we can just get you to where
you can avoid his little flower,

446
00:21:02,796 --> 00:21:04,631
- we’ll be in good shape.
- Gon: Osu!

447
00:21:04,665 --> 00:21:07,902
Narrator: Gon has won
his match against razor,

448
00:21:07,935 --> 00:21:10,638
but the bombers
are still far more powerful

449
00:21:10,671 --> 00:21:12,540
than his group of allies.

450
00:21:12,573 --> 00:21:16,043
Will they be able to find
a path to success?

451
00:21:16,076 --> 00:21:17,044
♪

452
00:21:17,077 --> 00:21:19,079
( Singing in Japanese )

